install scripts for various open source packages. installs them in your
homedirectory.

current need the following packages:
sudo apt-get install libssl-dev libbz2-dev libz-dev libc6-i386

not working on mac:
* sparsehash

basic compilation instructions
* cd src/PACKAGE/
* ./install.sh

this will compile the PACKAGE to build/PACKAGE-VERSION

to make PACKAGE available in your environment, run
* source setupenv.sh `latest.sh`

setupenv.sh sets all needed environment variables for a given list of packages
latest.sh generates a list of (newest versions of) packages found in the
build/ directory.
